article.headline: Navy 90, Lafayette 67
article.story: ANNAPOLIS, Md. -- Chris Harris scored 28 points to lead Navy to a 90-67 win over Lafayette on Saturday night. Clif Colbert added 19 points and six rebounds for the Midshipmen (17-8, 6-4 Patriot League). Kaleo Kina contributed 18 points, eight rebounds and nine assists. Navy used an 11-0 run in the first half to take a 31-18 lead with 10:08 remaining. The Midshipman led 50-35 at halftime. A separate 11-0 run in the second half was capped by a Colbert layup with 14:56 remaining, giving Navy a 62-39 lead. The Leopards (6-19, 2-8) were led by Michael Gruner, who scored 15. Ryan Willen added 14 points and 12 rebounds. The Midshipmen shot 50 percent from the field (35-for-70), and totaled 22 assists. They also shot 45 percent from 3-point range (9-for-20), and outrebounded Lafayette 44-34.
